  dr bergs probiotic has this in it

interesting because in the descriptions these strains mention one another as working in conjunction
"L. plantarum LM2 and L. brevis Y1 produce, respectively, Acetylcholine (Ach) 
  and Gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA)"

 lactobacillus rhamnosus and reuteri 
    some doctors and researchers are saying these strains are good 

B Infantis - Berg thinks this is very important and often missing, helps autoimmune diseases 

_________________

amazing berg video on keystone microbes: 
  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3QePHCO8T8Q

  1) prevotella - helps balance blood sugar. 
        eliminates oxylates 
        missing from 70%
  2) akkermansia - helps with producing gut mucosal lining 
          deficiency increases metabolic issue
          40-60% missing 
  3) faecalibacterium - reduces inflammation / counters autoimmune 
        30-50% missing 
  4) ruminococcus - 50-60% missing 
        deficiency means you can't digest certain fibers from plants 
